caption: I just love their dishes. I always get excellent service here. The place is neat and the cashiers are always kind. Would recommend to others.

It satisfies my cravings for coxinha and pastel in NYC! I go out of my way to eat at Petisco. I have both ordered for delivery as well as driving from Manhattan to Brooklyn. The service is wonderful! The owners are very sweet and always prompt tk help with your orders. 🇧🇷
One of my preferred places to grab some food. awesome location, clean, and good service. Keep it up!
Absolutely delicious and really authentic. Makes me miss Brasil! 🇧🇷
Very good place to have a taste of Brazil. The customer service is very good and the food is high quality.
Great atmosphere and great food especially the empanadas 😋. A taste of Brasil in Brooklyn.

We ordered the large option of empanadas. $10 for 4 empanadas which are almost empty, barely filled with cheese/chicken/beef. Honestly, for this price in this location I was expecting something else ...

Was really excited to find this place for Coxinhas! While they were experiencing some payment issues and sauce shortage when I visited the food was delicious. The chicken coxinhas and beef empanadas were amazing! Super friendly staff as well.
Food is very good ,but we buy feijoada and they serve beans and sausage Very good but iam very disappointed 😞
Great authentic Brazilian food!!!!

Nice ambiance.  The place is clean and the employees seem nice and personable which is good.  Unfortunately, that is the only memorable thing because it's better to forget everything else.  I had ordered a box of Coxinha's which had 30 pieces.  They messed up the order and didn't give me 3 flavors of 10 each, instead they gave me 15 pieces of the ridiculously dry Chicken Coxinha's and 5 of the Codfish balls.  The texture of the Coxinha's are not right and no way comparable to Brazil.  DO NOT ORDER THE CHICKEN COXINHA's.  The Feijoada was pretty much just beans and sausage.  The sausage had been stewed for so long it had no flavor to it whatsoever.  The rice was not aromatic or flavorful.  It's passable if you've never had the real thing.
Great just need other meats
Finest place to buy something when in a rush. Their service is prompt, prices are reasonable, fantastic character. I highly recommend this spot.
I'm glad to been there

Their food is always ON POINT! Fresh, delicious and authentically Brazilian. This is my go-to whenever I want to feel like home. Really proud of the owners Vanessa and Ricardo, they are the best!!!
Fun little filled fried balls . Great for sharing. Super clean spot.
Best food, super friendly staff, always  awesome atmosphere. They charge reasonable rates and the food quality is fantastic. 5 stars.

I've been here four times, trying different items on the menu and there hasn't been anything I didn't like. I recommend the beef jerk coxinha; that one is my favorite. But everything is delicious. The cashier that I've seen almost everytime I've been there is really nice and helpful. The decor is nice and the bathroom is really clean.

Tried the coxinha pastry, kielbasa, codfish, and spinach varieties. The pastry reminds me a little bit of a pierogi or small dumpling/dimsum. I liked the codfish one which was pretty good. However, neither the kielbasa nor the spinach reminded me of those flavors. Overall, I would say my experience with the food and the service was just ok.
Awesome Brazilian street food to go and some spaces to munch indoors! Great little spot and easy to park around.

Very easy to order online through their website. Had a little 4th of July party and the salgadinhos were a success. The appetizers came fresh and warm and they are delicious. As a Brazilian, I highly recommend Petisco Brazuca for your next gathering.
